{"word":"G1453 - ἐγείρω - egeírō - eg-i'-ro - Awake","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐγείρω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>egeírō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>eg-i'-ro"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Awake"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - உயிர்த்தெழு, எழுந்திரு, எழும்பு, எழு"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"rise"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Probably akin to the base of <a href=\"#/G58 - ἀγορά - agorá - ag-or-ah'/58\">G58</a> (through the idea of <i>collecting</i> one&rsquo;s faculties); to <i>waken</i> (transitively or intransitively), that is, <i>rouse</i> (literally from sleep, from sitting or lying, from disease, from death; or figuratively from obscurity, inactivity, ruins, nonexistence): - awake, lift (up), raise (again, up), rear up, (a-) rise (again, up), stand, take up."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1127 - γρηγορεύω - grēgoreúō - gray-gor-yoo'-o/1127\">G1127</a>, <a href=\"#/G1453 - ἐγείρω - egeírō - eg-i'-ro/1453\">G1453</a>, <a href=\"#/G1454 - ἔγερσις - égersis - eg'-er-sis/1454\">G1454</a>, <a href=\"#/G1825 - ἐξεγείρω - exegeírō - ex-eg-i'-ro/1825\">G1825</a>"}]}